                    <h3>Research for Health in Humanitarian Crises: Impact evaluation. 2023</h3>
                    <p><strong>With Anna Paterson, Megan Beare, Nici Dahrendorf, Faduma Gure, Basma Haj Ali & Hana Rohan. Elrha website.</strong></p>
                    <p>This evaluation looks at the impact after ten years of work supported by Elrha. Elhra is a global organisation "that finds solutions to complex humanitarian problems through research and innovation." This evaluation looks at the performance of the Research for Health in Humanitarian Crises (R2HC) programme of Elhra and considers its performance, the quality of research it supports and the niche it occupies.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.elrha.org/programme/research-for-health-in-humanitarian-crises/" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm" target="_blank">Read More</a>
                </div>

